Sentencas: Anode materials with excellent catalytic activity, good stability, and enhanced tolerance to carbon deposition are highly desired for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Herein, CoFe (CF) nanoalloy catalysts are homogeneously in-situ embedded on Sr-3 FeMoO7 (RP-SFM) efficient electrically conductive perovskite matrix through reduction of Sr2FeMo2/3Co1/3O6-delta precursor.
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The particle size of CoFe alloy is in the range of 10-50 nm, and the electrical conductivity enhances from about 8 to 17 S cm(-1) to 49-63 S cm(-1) after Sr2FeMo2/3Co1/3O6-delta reduction.
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of SOFCs with the RP-SFM@CF-SDC(Sm0.2Ce0.O-8(1.9)) composite anode in H-2 fuel reaches to 2.12 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, which is about 1.4 times than that of the SOFCs with traditional Ni-SDC anode.
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the RP-SFM@CF-SDC anodes also demonstrate excellent resistance to carbon deposition and high power density when C3H8 hydrocarbon is used as fuel.
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The improved catalytic activity results from the efficient electronic/ion conductive paths, abundant CoFe active sites, together with the enlarged trip phase boundaries (TPBs).
Titulo: In situ embedding of CoFe nanocatalysts into Sr3FeMoO7 matrix as high-performance anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells
